Luxury is not a vice. It is proof that destiny favors the deserving.
I find rebellion tedious. It always begins with rhetoric and ends with rope.
Titles granted by coin are fragile. Titles earned by blood are inconvenient.
The lower wards smell of spice, sweat, and desperation. How... atmospheric.
Nothing is more dangerous than a man who believes he has the moral high ground.
I have never lifted a sword. That is what retainers are for.
Influence is inherited by the wise and wasted by the sentimental.
Promise a man freedom and he will dream. Promise him privilege and he will kneel.
I do not command crowds. I command the ones who command them.
The city thrives because people like me are willing to guide it. Others merely exist within it.
I find hardship admirable. In other people.
Gold opens doors. The right lineage unlocks entire palaces.
Commoners admire strength. Nobles admire discretion.
A well-placed whisper can topple an army. Remember that.
Slavery may be distasteful to some, but it is exceedingly efficient.
The Chainbreakers? Children stomping in puddles, believing they cause the storm.
The pasha knows loyalty. That is why those with sense stand beside him.
I do not threaten. I simply mention outcomes.
It is not corruption if the city benefits.
I invest in stability. Violence is far too expensive.
